1.00	Meir_David_Kahane	Meir Kahane	Martin David Kahane (1 August 1932 – 5 November 1990), also known as Meir Kahane (Hebrew: ‎), was an American-Israeli rabbi and ultra-nationalist writer and political figure, whose work became either the direct or indirect foundation of most modern Jewish terrorist groups. He was an ordained Orthodox rabbi and later served as a member of the Israeli Knesset. Kahane also used the pen names Benyac and David Sinai and the pseudonyms Michael King, David Borac, and Martin Keene.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Kahane-tzadak.jpg/180px-Kahane-tzadak.jpg
